        @Timed
public javax.ws.rs.core.Response deleteExperiment(Experiment.ID experimentID,
                                                         @HeaderParam(value="Authorization")
                                                         String authorizationHeader)
        Deletes the specified experiment. An experiment can only be deleted if it is in either the "draft" or "terminated" states. This is a soft delete, hiding the experiment from the API without actually deleting it from the database.
        Parameters:
        experimentID - the experiment id
        authorizationHeader - the authorization headers
        Returns:
        Response object

      • exportAssignments

        @Timed
public javax.ws.rs.core.Response exportAssignments(Experiment.ID experimentID,
                                                          Context context,
                                                          String ignoreStringNullBucket,
                                                          String fromStringDate,
                                                          String toStringDate,
                                                          String timeZoneString,
                                                          @HeaderParam(value="Authorization")
                                                          String authorizationHeader)
                                                   throws ParseException
        Returns all user assignments for a given experiment ID. Will return null assignments as well as those assigned to buckets within the experiment
        Parameters:
        experimentID - the unique experiment ID
        context - context (PROD, QA, etc.); Optional.
        ignoreStringNullBucket - if null bucket should be ignored
        fromStringDate - the string formatted of the from date to download assignment
        toStringDate - the string formatted of the to date to download assignment
        timeZoneString - the string formatted of the timezone to use
        authorizationHeader - the authorization headers
        Returns:
        Response object containing metadata
        Throws:
        ParseException - when date or timezone failed to parse
